{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011rYLFFBFqY9Xw9GzovGY81","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01TdRrXomyuRcaANide9qoDf","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/dylan/.claude/plans/add-a-version-flag-recursive-dusk.md","content":"# Add `--version` flag to Go program\n\n## Context\nThe user wants `main.go` to support a `--version` flag that prints `v1.0.0` and exits, so the built binary can report its version. The current program (`main.go`) is a 3-line hello-world that only prints `\"hi\"`.\n\n## Change\nModify `main.go` to check command-line arguments before the existing logic. Use the standard `os` package (`os.Args`) rather than the heavier `flag` package, since we only need to detect a single flag and it keeps the tiny program simple.\n\nResulting `main.go`:\n```go\npackage main\n\nimport (\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"os\"\n)\n\nfunc main() {\n\tif len(os.Args) > 1 && (os.Args[1] == \"--version\" || os.Args[1] == \"-version\") {\n\t\tfmt.Println(\"v1.0.0\")\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\tfmt.Println(\"hi\")\n}\n```\n\nNotes:\n- `return` exits `main` cleanly (equivalent to exit code 0). `os.Exit(0)` is unnecessary here.\n- Accepting both `--version` and `-version` matches Go's conventional flag handling; if only `--version` is desired, this can be trimmed.\n\n## Verification\n- `go run . --version` â†’ prints `v1.0.0`\n- `go run .` â†’ prints `hi`\n- `go vet ./...` and `go build .` succeed with no errors\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10112,"cache_creation_input_tokens":162,"cache_read_input_tokens":31403,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":162},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"485C9666-33DB-4ABA-8AA0-5E7CDAE1943C","uuid":"43e4d105-605c-4bc3-9a29-74433ef03